1
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:44,300
"Unfold"

2
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:47,500
(Episode 4)

3
00:01:51,041 --> 00:01:52,708
That little girl I mentioned last time...

4
00:01:53,208 --> 00:01:54,708
her father jumped to his death.

5
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:59,416
After we talked that day,
I went back and did some digging.

6
00:01:59,416 --> 00:02:00,416
Take a look.

7
00:02:02,166 --> 00:02:04,000
The organ sources
matched with your father...

8
00:02:04,208 --> 00:02:05,528
all came from these hospitals.

9
00:02:05,958 --> 00:02:07,041
I had someone look into it.

10
00:02:07,125 --> 00:02:08,165
They were all accidents...

11
00:02:08,291 --> 00:02:09,571
that resulted in brain death.

12
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:12,124
The families' behavior was also strange.

13
00:02:12,125 --> 00:02:13,165
They were too cooperative.

14
00:02:14,708 --> 00:02:16,291
And they're private hospitals.

15
00:02:17,708 --> 00:02:18,500
Plus,

16
00:02:18,501 --> 00:02:19,665
these hospitals clearly knew

17
00:02:19,666 --> 00:02:21,041
about our organization,

18
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:23,041
yet they never reached out to us.

19
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,875
Except for Minhua Hospital.

20
00:02:30,375 --> 00:02:31,375
Come to think of it,

21
00:02:31,416 --> 00:02:32,624
during the handovers,

22
00:02:32,625 --> 00:02:33,707
the families seemed way too numb.

23
00:02:33,708 --> 00:02:34,790
Even if they were overwhelmed with grief,

24
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:35,911
they wouldn't act like that.

25
00:02:36,083 --> 00:02:37,291
In my experience,

26
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:40,293
we're lucky if the families
didn't lash out at us.

27
00:02:41,291 --> 00:02:42,000
Yeah.

28
00:02:42,291 --> 00:02:43,291
I've seen that firsthand.

29
00:02:45,166 --> 00:02:46,166
So,

30
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:48,791
you suspect the families were fake?

31
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:52,750
Thank you.

32
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:56,096
Let's eat first. We can talk while we eat.

33
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:02,625
Just helping out.

34
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Do you want some?

35
00:03:09,458 --> 00:03:10,458
Thank you.

36
00:03:16,541 --> 00:03:18,625
Do you usually eat alone?

37
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:23,832
My dad was rarely home,

38
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:25,333
so I just grab whatever.

39
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,808
You can come over to my place next time.

40
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,250
I'll cook for you.

41
00:03:36,791 --> 00:03:38,165
Didn't you say last time

42
00:03:38,166 --> 00:03:40,006
that the sweet and sour
ribs were pretty good?

43
00:03:46,458 --> 00:03:47,791
So,

44
00:03:48,541 --> 00:03:50,333
do you often cook for others?

45
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:53,541
No.

46
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:55,083
Then why...

47
00:04:02,791 --> 00:04:03,791
Just eat.

48
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:10,083
You still haven't told me.

49
00:04:10,084 --> 00:04:11,458
When are you coming over?

50
00:04:15,375 --> 00:04:17,208
Once I'm done dealing
with my dad's affairs.

51
00:04:18,916 --> 00:04:19,916
I'll be waiting.

52
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:21,570
I'll have the ribs ready for you.

53
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:47,291
Nanyang Hospital.

54
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:49,208
Type O blood.

55
00:05:10,913 --> 00:05:12,080
[Scene cleaning fee]

56
00:05:12,125 --> 00:05:14,375
Take a look. Do you still
need to sign to confirm?

57
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:16,625
No need.

58
00:05:27,606 --> 00:05:32,279
(...in a bathtub.)
(...must wait for police investigation.)

59
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:40,833
[Liver donated, type O
blood, donor last name Xie]

60
00:05:40,858 --> 00:05:42,749
For the eight patients
your father and I handled,

61
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,290
within two weeks of their admission,

62
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:45,540
these private hospitals

63
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:46,665
would miraculously find organ donors

64
00:05:46,666 --> 00:05:48,833
with matching blood types.

65
00:05:49,041 --> 00:05:50,361
That's too much of a coincidence.

66
00:05:53,708 --> 00:05:55,540
Now that you're working on your own,

67
00:05:55,541 --> 00:05:57,916
remember to ask them
for the files before you go.

68
00:05:58,208 --> 00:05:59,250
Things like

69
00:05:59,375 --> 00:06:01,416
autopsy certificates and death reports.

70
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:03,832
You don't want to handle
a body with some virus

71
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:05,673
or an unnatural death
without even knowing it.

72
00:06:06,708 --> 00:06:07,708
I got it.

73
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:10,559
I've already transferred the
twenty thousand yuan to you.

74
00:06:10,583 --> 00:06:12,457
Look at you, only sixteen,

75
00:06:12,458 --> 00:06:13,583
and making this much money.

76
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,120
You can spend it however
you want. How great is that?

77
00:06:17,416 --> 00:06:18,791
I'm just glad I could help.

78
00:06:20,208 --> 00:06:21,665
Only sixteen and making this much money...

79
00:06:21,666 --> 00:06:23,999
For the eight patients
your father and I handled,

80
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,332
within two weeks of their admission...

81
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:25,958
That's too much of a coincidence.

82
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:26,999
An organ donor would appear.

83
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,332
These private hospitals...

84
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:29,541
an organ donor would appear.

85
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:42,213
[Dad: July 28th, Mingyue Pavilion,
Hexi district #366, Unit 3, Room 702]

86
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:11,416
It's all taken care of.

87
00:07:11,417 --> 00:07:12,497
You just need to sign here.

88
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:57,500
Bai Che.

89
00:07:57,916 --> 00:07:58,916
Where are you going?

90
00:07:58,958 --> 00:07:59,958
I'll give you a ride.

91
00:08:07,666 --> 00:08:09,041
What were you doing just now?

92
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,820
Was it some kind of manual labor?

93
00:08:14,208 --> 00:08:15,458
You're sweating a lot.

94
00:08:17,458 --> 00:08:18,458
It's nothing.

95
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:20,916
Just some routine cleaning work.

96
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:25,833
Want me to take you out for a bite?

97
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:27,375
No, thanks.

98
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:29,231
I need to get back to the bookstore.

99
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:42,249
A'Che, the bookshelf outside is broken.

100
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:43,291
Should we get a new one?

101
00:09:15,541 --> 00:09:16,291
Don't worry.

102
00:09:16,292 --> 00:09:17,791
No one will find the ledger.

103
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:25,332
When your father and I did the handovers,

104
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:27,666
I saw him write down
some patient information.

105
00:10:27,521 --> 00:10:31,134
[A collection of dates, bits of information
like gender, blood type, and maybe hospitals?]

106
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:07,291
What's wrong?

107
00:11:09,583 --> 00:11:10,583
This afternoon,

108
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,250
I saw you wearing a hazmat suit.

109
00:11:14,916 --> 00:11:16,166
That was just...

110
00:11:16,666 --> 00:11:17,874
Don't tell me

111
00:11:17,875 --> 00:11:19,125
it was just "cleaning work."

112
00:11:40,041 --> 00:11:41,583
Why won't you tell me the truth?

113
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:52,791
I'm under no obligation to...

114
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:55,833
Can you just leave me in peace?

115
00:11:58,625 --> 00:11:59,625
Bai Che.

116
00:12:08,791 --> 00:12:10,791
Do you know what I cleaned up today?

117
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:14,875
It was a woman.

118
00:12:15,916 --> 00:12:16,958
Twenty-eight years old.

119
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:18,250
Type O blood.

120
00:12:19,708 --> 00:12:20,833
Her liver

121
00:12:21,125 --> 00:12:22,000
is probably inside

122
00:12:22,001 --> 00:12:23,791
that little girl's body right now.

123
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:42,291
Do you think I'm complicit in this?

124
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,083
That's not what I meant.

125
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:47,375
Then what do you mean?

126
00:12:47,875 --> 00:12:48,916
You suspect me?

127
00:12:49,375 --> 00:12:50,375
I don't.

128
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,000
I'm just scared.

129
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:54,750
Scared of what?

130
00:12:57,291 --> 00:12:58,708
Scared that you'll get hurt.

131
00:12:59,125 --> 00:13:00,845
Scared that I won't be able to protect you.

132
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,000
Just leave.

133
00:13:21,166 --> 00:13:22,166
I'm closing up.

134
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:32,250
Go.

